<subSubSection lastPageId="152" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="149.[151,1437,1329,2041]" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1474,1500]" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier" box="[322,483,1474,1501]" firstAuthor="Olivier" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" pagination="183 - 187" refId="ref120180" refString="Olivier, E. (1886) In: Baer, G. - A., Catalogue des Coleopteres des Iles Philippines. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1886, 183 - 187." type="journal article" year="1886">Olivier (1886)</bibRefCitation>
described a 
<quantity box="[623,701,1473,1500]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
long male from the 
<collectingCountry box="[928,1054,1474,1500]" name="Philippines" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1068,1139,1474,1501]" country="Philippines" name="Bohol" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Bohol</collectingRegion>
) as totally yellow dorsally and with a single recurved appendage of the terminal abdomen. Subsequently (1913b) he indicated the occurrence of the species from Borneo, but this time the abdomen having “two long elevated appendicles curved upwards”. He did not however list any specimens. It is possible the first specimen may have been a species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1939" box="[1206,1341,1582,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1341,1582,1608]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or even a female, while the second specimen could have been a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1833" box="[766,892,1618,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Colophotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[766,892,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Colophotia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. The single male identified by Blair in NHML conforms in both size and colour to 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier" box="[565,727,1654,1681]" firstAuthor="Olivier" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" pagination="183 - 187" refId="ref120180" refString="Olivier, E. (1886) In: Baer, G. - A., Catalogue des Coleopteres des Iles Philippines. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1886, 183 - 187." type="journal article" year="1886">Olivier (1886)</bibRefCitation>
but the abdomen to neither description (the specimen was not dissected). 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1883" box="[276,499,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis box="[276,412,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Luciola lata</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
, which was described with a median carina on the last abdominal segment, is a large pale species from Borneo, and was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1880" box="[761,1006,1726,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallescens">
<emphasis box="[761,908,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">L. pallescens</emphasis>
Gorham
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="McDermott" box="[1048,1264,1726,1753]" firstAuthor="McDermott" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref119380" refString="McDermott, F. A. (1966) Lampyridae. In: Steel, W. O. (Ed.), Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 9. Editio Secunda. W. Junk, S'Gravenhage, pp. 1 - 149." type="book chapter" year="1966">McDermott (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. The latter species is addressed here and assigned to 
<emphasis box="[572,705,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne Lambkin &amp; Fu" authorityYear="2013" box="[572,701,1762,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Abscondita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Abscondita</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1883" box="[757,829,1762,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis box="[757,829,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">L. lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
addressed below. None of the specimens we examined have any suggestion of a median carina on 
<date box="[634,671,1798,1824]" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">V7</date>
, and McDermott’s synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1883" box="[1040,1084,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis box="[1040,1084,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1880" box="[1148,1265,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallescens">
<emphasis box="[1148,1265,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">pallescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rejected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="149.[151,1437,1329,2041]" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
The issue is further confused as several 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1857" box="[639,759,1834,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciolinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="149" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Luciolinae</taxonomicName>
have large females which approach 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier's" box="[1161,1340,1834,1861]" firstAuthor="Olivier's" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" pagination="183 - 187" refId="ref120180" refString="Olivier, E. (1886) In: Baer, G. - A., Catalogue des Coleopteres des Iles Philippines. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1886, 183 - 187." type="journal article" year="1886">Olivier’s (1886)</bibRefCitation>
description of 
